            <p>29 South 6th. St.<lb/></p>
            <p>My Dear Sir.<lb/></p>
            <p>Please present to your<lb/> congregation during the Pasach holi&#45;<lb/>days the claims of the Alliance Israe&#45;<lb/>lite Universelle on the Jewish commu&#45;<lb/>nity.  I cannot suggest to you the<lb/> importance and merits of this society<lb/> as you doubtless know them better<lb/> than I do.  The Alliance is seeking<lb/> to increase its sphere of usefulness<lb/> by extending its operations in the es&#45;<lb/>tablishment of schools in localities<lb/> where hitherto the Jewish population have<lb/> received but little recognition by their<lb/> western <sic>bretheren</sic>.  These additional<lb/> enterprises demand additional drafts<lb/> on a treasury that is not sufficient<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>for its present obligations.  In conse&#45;<lb/>quence of the outrages perpetrated on<lb/> the Russian Jews the receipts and funds<lb/> of the Philadelphia society were devoted<lb/> by it to them&#44; hence it is hoped that<lb/> generous subscriptions will be made<lb/> this year in order to supply the defic&#45;<lb/>iency caused by a diversion of the<lb/> funds to our Russian <sic>bretheren</sic>.<lb/></p>
            <p>Truly Yours.<lb/>
                Moses A. Dropsie<lb/>
                President A. U. I.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais	April 19 1883<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
